.TH UTILITYKIT 1 "July 2026" "UtilityKit v5.10.6" "UtilityKit Tools"
.SH NAME
utility-file_watcher \- Run a command whenever files matching a glob change. Supports inotify (Linux),
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B utility file_watcher
[\fIoptions\fP]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Run a command whenever files matching a glob change. Supports inotify (Linux),
.SH USAGE
.PP
.EX
watch -p '*.sh' -c 'make test'
watch -d ./src -p '*.py' -p '*.js' -c 'npm test' --debounce 2
watch -p '*' --polling 5 -c 'rsync -a . backup/'
watch --initial -c './build.sh' .
.EE
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
Flag   |   Meaning   |   Default
\fC-p, --pattern GLOB\fP   |   Watch pattern (repeatable)   |   all files
\fC-d, --dir DIR\fP   |   Watch directory   |   \fC.\fP
\fC-c, --cmd CMD\fP   |   Command   |   —
\fC-s, --debounce N\fP   |   Debounce seconds   |   1
\fC-i, --ignore GLOB\fP   |   Ignore pattern   |   —
\fC-r, --initial\fP   |   Run once on start   |   off
\fC--polling N\fP   |   Force polling interval   |   auto
.PP
.SH BACKENDS
.PP
.IP \(em 4
\fBinotifywait\fP — Linux (\fCapt install inotify-tools\fP)
.IP \(em 4
\fBfswatch\fP — macOS/Termux (\fCbrew install fswatch\fP)
.IP \(em 4
\fBpoll\fP — universal fallback (pure bash \fCfind\fP + \fCstat\fP)
